1. -- (1. d4 f5 {The Classical Dutch has had an exciting history. It has been
used as a weapon of choice by many well-known players who are famous for their
aggressive and creative styles. --- Indeed, a number of world champions and
challengers have used the opening, such as Morphy, Alekhine, Capablanca,
Botvinnik, Bronstein, Spassky, Korchnoi and Tal - an impressive list! --- The
Dutch Defence was discovered by the Dutchman Stein, hence the name of the
opening. Elias Stein was born in Holland in 1748, and he pointed out the
similarities between the Dutch Defence and the Sicilian Defence. If you look
at the first move, you can see that the two openings are similar, due to the
fact that the initial pawn structures of both openings are actually mirror
images of one another.}) (1. e4 c5 {Given the popularity of the Sicilian
Defence, I do find it surprising that the Dutch is not as well-liked.
Hopefully, over the course of this book, I can change any negative
pre-conceptions that you may have of this opening! --- The Dutch has had a
turbulent life, with grandmasters and even world champions differing in their
personal opinion of the opening. For example, Wilhelm Steinitz condemned the
opening after he defeated Zukertort, who used it in a match against him. On
the other hand the great Alexander Alekhine used the Dutch on a regular basis,
and had some great victories with the opening. --- It is fair to say that
nowadays the Classical Dutch has a dubious reputation, but who knows what the
world will think of the opening in 20 years from now!?}) *

