particularly dynamic but Black has no obvious weaknesses. I would suggest
playing in this manner if you have some knowledge of the Stonewall Dutch, as
this will help you find the right continuation.}) ({2) Daniel Fernandez has
suggested a particularly odd way of playing the position. I do admire his
imagination but I also have my doubts about his recommended way of playing.
Let's take a look...} 9... Nxc3 10. bxc3 a4 11. e4 Ra5 $5 {. If this works
then I am a monkey's bum! White has a big centre and it is not entirely clear
as to what Black is intending to do. Below are some sample lines that Daniel
and his chess engine prepared...} 12. -- (12. Rb1 fxe4 13. Qxe4 Rff5 $5 {
Black's rook has found a square which places some pressure along the kingside.
This position could well be playable.}) (12. e5 Nd7 13. Bf4 g5 {, with a messy
