the first chapter, you should understand why Black now plays this move. ---
BRAINSTORMING POINT! --- 1) If White can achieve the e4 advance without Black
playing ...e5 and Black has to exchange with ...fxe4, White will generally
obtain an advantage. --- 2) If Black can achieve the ...e5 advance, he will
have gained an equal position. --- This is the reason behind Black playing ...e5. The only problem with this move is that Black must sacrifice a pawn. Black
believes that he will have enough activity in return for the pawn but this is
probably not the case.} (11... Qxe4 12. Nh4 {wins the black queen! White is
better here.}) 12. Re1 {White's rook was now under attack as the threat was 12.
..Qxe4 and if 13 Nh4 then 13...Qg4 leaves Black with a substantial material
