to creep a bit nearer to White's king...} 21. Bxd4 {White sensibly swaps off
this strong piece.} exd4 {White now has to decide whether he should grab the
pawn on b7.} 22. Bxb7 {A very greedy decision, as White's bishop is shut out
of the game on b7 after Black's next move.} ({A more reasonable approach would
have been to play} 22. c5 {and White can attempt a pawn storm on the queenside,
for example,} c6 23. b4 {, but the position is still pretty equal.}) 22... c6 {
