on for a bit...} Bg6 19. Nf2 Nc5 20. Bd2 Nxe4 21. Nxe4 Bxe4 {Black is a bit
better here, mainly because the bishop on e4 is such a strong piece. I can
play on without any risk, although whether the position is good enough to win
is another matter. I expect that the position should be a win for Black.} 22.
Rf1 Rf8 23. Rxf8+ Kxf8 {I can now try to win by moving my king up to h3 and by
advancing my kingside pawns.} 24. Kf2 h5 {Stopping g4 and gaining space. White
