This pawn has to be constantly defended.} 25. Bc3 Ke7 26. b4 Kf6 27. a3 g6 28.
Bb3 Kf5 29. h3 {White has to stop my king from advancing to g4.} Bb1 30. Kf3
Be4+ 31. Kf2 g5 32. Bd1 g4 33. hxg4+ hxg4 34. Bb3 b5 $5 {This looked like a
good idea at the time. The simple plan is to play ...Bd3 and then ...Ke4.} ({
