allows Black's knight into a very strong square:} Nb4 {with ...Nd3 to follow.})
16... Ba3 $1 17. Rc2 $6 {This is an error after which White gets into some
serious problems.} ({It would have been wiser to have sacrificed the exchange
with} 17. bxc4 $1 {. At least this way White gains a slight initiative. Black
is still doing well though, for example,} Bxc1 18. Qxc1 Rc8 $1 {This is the
best square for the rook for tactical reasons. It looks more natural to place
the rook on b8, but having the rook on c8 allows Black the option of playing ...c5 at some point. Black is now planning to play ...Ne7 and at the correct
moment ...Bc6.} (18... Rb8 $6 {is correct in principle but runs into some
