20... Bb2 $1 {Taking advantage of some tactical tricks against the pawn on d4.
The rest of the game just requires some care on my part and the point is mine.}
21. Qe1 (21. Rxb2 $2 Qxd4+ 22. e3 Qxb2 {.}) 21... Qxd4+ 22. e3 (22. Be3 Qxe5
23. Bxa7 Bd4+ 24. Bxd4 Qxd4+ 25. Qf2 Qd6 {and Black has a big advantage.}) (22.
Qf2 Bg6 {.}) 22... Qd3 $1 {The resulting position after some exchanges is
winning for Black.} 23. Rxb2 Rxb2 24. Bxa5 Rc2 $1 {White is running out of
