Black wants to play ...e5 on the next move and gain a perfectly respectable
position. White must stop this by acting quickly.} 8. d5 $1 {The only way to
gain an advantage. Other options will be looked at later on.} Ne5 {In this
game, we will look at what happens when White does not play the critical 9 Nd4.
} 9. b3 $6 {BRAINSTORMING POINT! --- Black should be fine after this move. The
moves dxe6 or Nd4 are much more challenging for Black. --- How do you think
Black should continue?} Nxf3+ $1 {As a rule, if White does not play 9 Nd4 or 9
dxe6 then Black should continue with 9...Nxf3+ and 10...e5.} 10. exf3 (10. Bxf3
e5 {and Black has very good control of the centre.}) 10... e5 $1 {We have seen
this idea before!} 11. f4 {Trying to dispose of his doubled f-pawns. Black
also had ideas of playing ...f4 himself.} exf4 ({Other options include:} 11...
