promising plan where Black will try to gain control of the dark squares.}) (
11... e4 12. f3 {is better for White.}) 12. Bxf4 Ng4 $5 {Black manoeuvres his
pieces to better squares by placing his dark-squared bishop on f6 and knight
on e5.} 13. Bc1 $6 {This is rather slow. White should not lose control of the
f4-square as Black will play ...f4 himself, which could prove to be dangerous
for White.} ({In the past, White has also played} 13. Qc2 $1 {which is a
better plan. That game continued} Bf6 14. Rae1 Bd7 (14... Ne5 {is worth
