White avoids fianchettoing kingside then Black should aim to fianchetto
queenside.} 6. Bd3 Bb7 7. f3 $1 {This is the most sensible plan. White should
really stop a black piece from landing on e4.} c5 {This is another typical
plan. Black strikes out on the dark squares. I was aiming to finish my
development by playing ...d6 and ...Nbd7 when all of my pieces are working in
harmony.} 8. a3 $6 {I am not too keen on this move as there is no real rush to
