{This is a very important section as both the Colle and the London systems are
extremely popular at club level. I can guarantee that at some point during
your Classical Dutch playing career, you will face at least one of these
systems. To my knowledge, there is no literature available that shows how
exponents of the Classical Dutch should play against such systems. With this
in mind, I have spent some time looking for an aggressive set-up. My findings
are documented in this chapter:} 1. -- {The Colle System is an opening where
White adopts the same set-up against any black defence. White will often play
1 d4, 2 Nf3, 3 e3, 4 Bd3, 5 0-0 etc. This system is less effective against the
Dutch compared to the London system.} *

