time!}) 4. e4 $1 {and thanks to the space advantage in the centre, White has a
comfortable position. --- In addition, Black's king can also come under attack
after an exchange on e4 takes place. This is the type of position that I would
aim to avoid.}) 3. Bg5 $1 {This appears to be the most testing move.} ({White
has also tried:} 3. Bf4 {when I believe that} a6 $1 {stopping Nb5 is the best
